UI/UX Design Tip 

Always choose the chart type carefully! 

Line charts might look trendier but they don't apply to every case. 

When the x-axis has limited options, a bar chart is the correct graph type.

Plus, the line chart might introduce false intermediate values.

UI/UX Tip 

De-emphasize dangerous actions like deletion

You have to prioritize the default action instead of the dangerous/irreversible one. 

Also, use more than one ways to make it look like a secondary action (color, size, type, placement, etc).
